
[1]epicure

   EP'ICURE, n. [L. epicurus, a voluptuary, from Epicurus.]

   Properly, a follower of Epicurus; a man devoted to sensual enjoyments;
   hence, one who indulges in the luxuries of the table. [The word is now
   used only or chiefly in the latter sense.
